<p>I am creating this issue against the views module, but maybe the "component" shouldn't be views since the issue regards dropbutton...</p>
<p>The "List additional actions" button shown in the "dropbutton" widget needs two important accessibility improvements:</p>
<ol><li>After being clicked and showing the additional actions, the button label should become "Hide additional actions" (since clicking the button again will hide the additional actions);</li>
<li>The button should have some help text (as it happens using the "title" attribute for a link) to let an user understand what the button does (I think also this text should be different when additional actions are shown or not to reflect the button label);</li>
</ol>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1351320556;}i:7;a:10:{s:5:"title";s:27:"In-place editing for Fields";s:4:"link";s:30:"http://drupal.org/node/1824500";s:11:"description";s:9636:"<h3 id="summary-problem-motivation">Problem/Motivation</h3>
<p>When you want to fix a typo, or restructure your paragraphs, or quickly add another tag to your blog post, you always have to go to the <code>node/%/edit</code> page. Once you're there, you have to navigate through a potentially enormous form to find the particular thing you want to edit.</p>
<p>Even if <span class="project-issue-status-8 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1510532" title="Status: needs review">#1510532: Implement the new create content page design</a></span> gets done (which will make the above less painful), it is still much slower to have to navigate to another page to be able to edit the thing that you're currently viewing (i.e. you see <em>exactly</em> where the mistake is, you know <em>exactly</em> where you want to edit content).</p>
<p>Imagine you were able to edit those things right there, in-place?</p>
<p>Sound like science fiction? This is becoming standard fare in most other CMS/CMF/? software. Drupal 8 needs to have this feature out of the box in order to remain competitive.</p>
<h3 id="summary-proposed-resolution">Proposed resolution</h3>
<p>Add in-place editing to Drupal 8 core:</p>
<p><a href="http://drupal.org/files/project-images/edit-title-direct.png" class="imagecache imagecache-grid-3 imagecache-imagelink imagecache-grid-3_imagelink" rel="nofollow"><img src="/files/imagecache/grid-3/project-images/edit-title-direct.png" alt="Screenshot of editing the node title in-place" title="" class="imagecache imagecache-grid-3" width="220" height="36" /></a><br /><a href="http://drupal.org/files/project-images/edit-author-form.png" class="imagecache imagecache-grid-3 imagecache-imagelink imagecache-grid-3_imagelink" rel="nofollow"><img src="/files/imagecache/grid-3/project-images/edit-author-form.png" alt="Screenshot of editing the node author in-place" title="" class="imagecache imagecache-grid-3" width="220" height="63" /></a><br /><a href="http://drupal.org/files/project-images/edit-body-direct-wysiwyg.png" class="imagecache imagecache-grid-3 imagecache-imagelink imagecache-grid-3_imagelink" rel="nofollow"><img src="/files/imagecache/grid-3/project-images/edit-body-direct-wysiwyg.png" alt="Screenshot of editing the node body in-place" title="" class="imagecache imagecache-grid-3" width="220" height="131" /></a></p>
<p>On the PHP side, we implement <code>hook_preprocess_field()</code> to annotate fields with classes and data attributes so the JS side knows what to do. <code>_edit_analyze_field_editability()</code> figures whether and how each field should be editable.<br />
Edit.module is &lt;400 LoC, the form logic is &lt;150 LoC, AJAX page callbacks are &lt;200 LoC.</p>
<p><strong>We're looking for reviews on everything <em>except</em> for JS for now</strong> (please wait with reviewing the JS until <span class="project-issue-status-1 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1824100" title="Status: active">#1824100: Convert edit module JavaScript to use Create.js, VIE, and Backbone (D8)</a></span> is in).</p>
<p>It is not yet 100% ready, but in the spirit of <em>review early, reroll often</em>, here it already is for review.</p>
<h3 id="summary-remaining-tasks">Remaining tasks</h3>
<ul><li>Already in: <span class="project-issue-status-2 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1782838" title="Status: fixed, Assigned to: sun">#1782838: WYSIWYG in core: round one ? filter types</a></span></li>
<li>Already in: <span class="project-issue-status-2 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1149866" title="Status: fixed, Assigned to: nod_">#1149866: Add Backbone.js and Underscore.js to core</a></span></li>
<li>Patch with Field API refinements is already up for review: <span class="project-issue-status-15 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1821906" title="Status: patch (to be ported), Assigned to: Wim Leers">#1821906: Allow more Field API public API functions to act on a single field within an entity</a></span>.</li>
</ul><p>Remaining tasks:</p>
<ul><li>Critical: <span class="project-issue-status-1 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1824100" title="Status: active">#1824100: Convert edit module JavaScript to use Create.js, VIE, and Backbone (D8)</a></span> (will be worked on by @frega, @bergie and myself during BADCamp)</li>
<li>Critical: <span class="project-issue-status-1 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1823898" title="Status: active, Assigned to: Wim Leers">#1823898: Get rid of the _edit_get_wysiwyg_info() + hook_edit_wysiwyg_info() travesty, convert to the plugin system.</a></span> </li>
<li>Critical: <span class="project-issue-status-1 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1741122" title="Status: active, Assigned to: Wim Leers">#1741122: Validation support: validation errors currently result in JS alert()s with JSON barf</a></span></li>
<li>Critical: <span class="project-issue-status-1 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1823894" title="Status: active">#1823894: Improve Edit's "Editbar"</a></span></li>
</ul><p>Follow-ups (after this gets committed):</p>
<ul><li>Get rid of <code>edit_entity_access()</code> (which returns <code>FALSE</code> for all entity types other than nodes) once <span class="project-issue-status-13 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1696660" title="Status: needs work">#1696660: Add an entity access API</a></span> lands.</li>
<li>Get rid of <code>edit_entity_allows_revisions()</code>: Entity API should be able to tell us if a user is allowed to create a new revision or not. Alas, I wasn't able to find a clean way to do that.</li>
<li>Add integration with Aloha Editor when <span class="project-issue-status-8 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1809702" title="Status: needs review">#1809702: WYSIWYG in core:  round two ? Aloha.module (Aloha Editor)</a></span> lands.</li>
<li>Minor: <code>Drupal.ajax</code> is a nightmare to interact with for Edit's JS, see <span class="project-issue-status-1 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1533366#comment-6151610" title="Status: active">#1533366-3: Refactor Drupal.ajax</a></span> for details.</li>
<li>Critical: <span class="project-issue-status-4 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1678002" title="Status: postponed">#1678002: Move save/cancel to toolbar rather than per-field basis, auto-revisions on edit (with automatic log messages)</a></span></li>
</ul><p>And last but most definitely not least: how to deal with accessibility? Does it even make sense to support in-place editing for people who use screen readers? Would it be more efficient for them to continue to go to the <code>node/%/edit</code> page and use the form there?<br />
Starting point: <span class="project-issue-status-1 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1747916" title="Status: active, Assigned to: Wim Leers">#1747916: (selected tab) indicator does not change on View/Edit</a></span>.</p>
<h3 id="summary-ui-changes">User interface changes</h3>
<ul><li>No UI changes on the back-end.</li>
<li>Whenever there is at least one field that the current user is allowed to edit, the Editbar shows up. It contains a "View/Quick edit" toggle, it is set to "View" by default. If the user toggles it, all content will fade away except for the fields that are editable. You can then click on any of them to edit them in-place.</li>
<li><code>type=direct</code> editing:<br /><a href="http://drupal.org/files/project-images/edit-title-direct.png" class="imagecache imagecache-grid-3 imagecache-imagelink imagecache-grid-3_imagelink" rel="nofollow"><img src="/files/imagecache/grid-3/project-images/edit-title-direct.png" alt="Screenshot of editing the node title in-place" title="" class="imagecache imagecache-grid-3" width="220" height="36" /></a>
  </li>
<li><code>type=form</code> editing:<br /><a href="http://drupal.org/files/project-images/edit-author-form.png" class="imagecache imagecache-grid-3 imagecache-imagelink imagecache-grid-3_imagelink" rel="nofollow"><img src="/files/imagecache/grid-3/project-images/edit-author-form.png" alt="Screenshot of editing the node author in-place" title="" class="imagecache imagecache-grid-3" width="220" height="63" /></a>
  </li>
<li><code>type=direct-with-wysiwyg</code> editing:<br /><a href="http://drupal.org/files/project-images/edit-body-direct-wysiwyg.png" class="imagecache imagecache-grid-3 imagecache-imagelink imagecache-grid-3_imagelink" rel="nofollow"><img src="/files/imagecache/grid-3/project-images/edit-body-direct-wysiwyg.png" alt="Screenshot of editing the node body in-place" title="" class="imagecache imagecache-grid-3" width="220" height="131" /></a>
  </li>
</ul><h3 id="summary-api-changes">API changes</h3>
<ul><li>Once <span class="project-issue-status-1 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1823898" title="Status: active, Assigned to: Wim Leers">#1823898: Get rid of the _edit_get_wysiwyg_info() + hook_edit_wysiwyg_info() travesty, convert to the plugin system.</a></span> is addressed, there will be a new type of plugin.</li>
<li>Formatters must now indicate the editability of textual fields explicitly (because only those can be edited with <code>type=direct</code> or <code>type=direct-with-wysiwyg</code>): see the changes to text.module?s formatters, plus <a href="http://drupalcode.org/project/edit.git/blob/d3a6777e2953a72612fc2e98b93c3fa527f873c0:/includes/text.inc" title="http://drupalcode.org/project/edit.git/blob/d3a6777e2953a72612fc2e98b93c3fa527f873c0:/includes/text.inc" rel="nofollow">http://drupalcode.org/project/edit.git/blob/d3a6777e2953a72612fc2e98b93c...</a> for docs. I?m not sure where and how this should be documented?</li>
</ul>";s:8:"comments";s:39:"http://drupal.org/node/1824500#comments";s:8:"category";s:97:"accessibilityin-place editingJavaScriptneeds accessibility reviewNeeds testsSparkUsabilitywysiwyg";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Fri, 26 Oct 2012 21:28:14 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"Wim Leers";}s:4:"guid";s:28:"1824500 at http://drupal.org";s:7:"summary";s:9636:"<h3 id="summary-problem-motivation">Problem/Motivation</h3>
<p>When you want to fix a typo, or restructure your paragraphs, or quickly add another tag to your blog post, you always have to go to the <code>node/%/edit</code> page. Once you're there, you have to navigate through a potentially enormous form to find the particular thing you want to edit.</p>
<p>Even if <span class="project-issue-status-8 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1510532" title="Status: needs review">#1510532: Implement the new create content page design</a></span> gets done (which will make the above less painful), it is still much slower to have to navigate to another page to be able to edit the thing that you're currently viewing (i.e. you see <em>exactly</em> where the mistake is, you know <em>exactly</em> where you want to edit content).</p>
