</div>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1346702153;}i:26;a:10:{s:5:"title";s:57:"Build a consistent, accessibile approach to using Sprites";s:4:"link";s:30:"http://drupal.org/node/1744838";s:11:"description";s:1173:"<p>We have some sprites in core and we'll have more:<br /><span class="project-issue-status-3 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/851496" title="Status: closed (duplicate)">#851496: Invalid to use the CSS background to display non-background images</a></span><br /><span class="project-issue-status-7 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/821672" title="Status: closed (fixed)">#821672: Forum icons not accessible to screen-reader users</a></span></p>
<p>There are some new best practices that should be considered<br /><a href="http://www.paciellogroup.com/blog/2012/08/notes-on-accessible-css-image-sprites/" title="http://www.paciellogroup.com/blog/2012/08/notes-on-accessible-css-image-sprites/" rel="nofollow">http://www.paciellogroup.com/blog/2012/08/notes-on-accessible-css-image-...</a><br /><a href="http://openweb.eu.org/articles/performances_web_les_sprites_CSS" title="http://openweb.eu.org/articles/performances_web_les_sprites_CSS" rel="nofollow">http://openweb.eu.org/articles/performances_web_les_sprites_CSS</a></p>
<p>And how we approach this needs to be consistent so that it is easy for modules to adopt this best practice moving forward.</p>
";s:8:"comments";s:39:"http://drupal.org/node/1744838#comments";s:8:"category";s:28:"accessibilitymobilespriteWPO";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 22 Aug 2012 21:39:58 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:8:"mgifford";}s:4:"guid";s:28:"1744838 at http://drupal.org";s:7:"summary";s:1173:"<p>We have some sprites in core and we'll have more:<br /><span class="project-issue-status-3 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/851496" title="Status: closed (duplicate)">#851496: Invalid to use the CSS background to display non-background images</a></span><br /><span class="project-issue-status-7 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/821672" title="Status: closed (fixed)">#821672: Forum icons not accessible to screen-reader users</a></span></p>
<p>There are some new best practices that should be considered<br /><a href="http://www.paciellogroup.com/blog/2012/08/notes-on-accessible-css-image-sprites/" title="http://www.paciellogroup.com/blog/2012/08/notes-on-accessible-css-image-sprites/" rel="nofollow">http://www.paciellogroup.com/blog/2012/08/notes-on-accessible-css-image-...</a><br /><a href="http://openweb.eu.org/articles/performances_web_les_sprites_CSS" title="http://openweb.eu.org/articles/performances_web_les_sprites_CSS" rel="nofollow">http://openweb.eu.org/articles/performances_web_les_sprites_CSS</a></p>
