<p>Found here:<br /><a href="http://www.otakunozoku.com/php-imploded-wrap/" title="http://www.otakunozoku.com/php-imploded-wrap/" rel="nofollow">http://www.otakunozoku.com/php-imploded-wrap/</a></p>
";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1342447068;}i:29;a:10:{s:5:"title";s:56:"Improve how aria-describedby is applied to form elements";s:4:"link";s:30:"http://drupal.org/node/1666242";s:11:"description";s:1278:"<p>In <span class="project-issue-status-7 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/405360" title="Status: closed (fixed)">#405360: Use aria-describedby to link form elements with form element descriptions</a></span> aria-describedby is applied to some form elements, to programmatically associate them with form element descriptions.</p>
<p>In <span class="project-issue-status-13 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/933004#comment-6172410" title="Status: needs work">#933004-16: Require #title for all form elements</a></span> a more abstracted method of automating manipulation of form elements is recommended, by adding a process callback.</p>
<p>I recommend that we revisit the aria-describedby work, and convert to the process callback method.</p>
<p>Every element description is provided a unique ID<br />
Every element that could make use of a aria-describedby relationship (textfield yes, tableselect no) has a process callback added by default to check for a description, and if present to apply the aria-describedby attribute.</p>
<p>This means that newly created elements that would benefit from aria-describedby can simply reference the same process callback function, and that those wishing to remove the aria-describedby can simply remove the callback.</p>
";s:8:"comments";s:39:"http://drupal.org/node/1666242#comments";s:8:"category";s:17:"accessibilityaria";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Sat, 30 Jun 2012 08:36:55 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:14:"Everett Zufelt";}s:4:"guid";s:28:"1666242 at http://drupal.org";s:7:"summary";s:1278:"<p>In <span class="project-issue-status-7 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/405360" title="Status: closed (fixed)">#405360: Use aria-describedby to link form elements with form element descriptions</a></span> aria-describedby is applied to some form elements, to programmatically associate them with form element descriptions.</p>
<p>In <span class="project-issue-status-13 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/933004#comment-6172410" title="Status: needs work">#933004-16: Require #title for all form elements</a></span> a more abstracted method of automating manipulation of form elements is recommended, by adding a process callback.</p>
<p>I recommend that we revisit the aria-describedby work, and convert to the process callback method.</p>
<p>Every element description is provided a unique ID<br />
Every element that could make use of a aria-describedby relationship (textfield yes, tableselect no) has a process callback added by default to check for a description, and if present to apply the aria-describedby attribute.</p>
<p>This means that newly created elements that would benefit from aria-describedby can simply reference the same process callback function, and that those wishing to remove the aria-describedby can simply remove the callback.</p>
