<h3>Accessibility considerations</h3>
<ul><li><strong>More than color</strong>: Drupal must use more than color alone to indicate which fields have errors. This is a major <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG-TECHS/F81.html" rel="nofollow">WCAG violation</a> that we didn't solve for Drupal 7.</li>
<li><strong>Links jump to errors</strong>: The $messages area at the top of the page will provide <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG-TECHS/G139.html" rel="nofollow">links to jump to errors</a> as WCAG suggests.</li>
