";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1315477326;}i:44;a:10:{s:5:"title";s:57:"No semantics for nested comments / bad for screen-readers";s:4:"link";s:30:"http://drupal.org/node/1272870";s:11:"description";s:908:"<p>Browsing through open issues I found <span class="project-issue-status-1 project-issue-status-info"><a href="/node/1272504" title="Status: active">#1272504: Display of nested comments is baffling and confusing</a></span>.</p>
<p>This reminded me that one of the major issues with comments is that there is no semantic parent-child relationship between nested comments.</p>
<p>If you look through a list of nested comments with CSS disabled, or using a screen-reader, there is nothing to signify if any particular comment is "in<br />
reply" to another.</p>
<p>I'm not sure if this is able to be dealt with in comment.tpl.php, or if it needs to be addressed in the wrapper, or somewhere else.</p>
